SIMPLE: inflated
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inflated
<hw>In*flat"ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Filled,
as with air or gas; blown up; distended; <as>as, a balloon
<ex>inflated</ex> with gas</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Turgid; swelling; puffed up; bombastic; pompous;
<as>as, an <ex>inflated</ex> style</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Inflated</qex> and astrut with self-conceit.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Hollow and distended, as a
perianth, corolla, nectary, or pericarp.</def>
<rj><au>Martyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Distended or enlarged fictitiously or without due
cause; <as>as, <ex>inflated</ex> prices; <ex>inflated</ex> expectations,
etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inflater</ent>⟦br⟧
